column5: i'm not sure if i should go fishing tommorow...its cold and the only way i would go is if it were still fishing...steelhead...are the trout  in the harbours like goderich where i can cast and wait? i'm asking is this an option ?
anyone else have a better answer?
How about get off the couch and find out for yourself for once... and report back so another couch potato can get out based on your advise!
no... i'm just sayin is it iced over?
There's ice, not sure about the fish though.. Got out this morning but no luck. Only 3 inches of ice where I was.
Goderich looked pretty open on Thursday... . but there's a group of PEng's from Denver that are looking for new employment !!
do you think i should try the harbours?
yeah i went and didn't catch anything because of the bad conditions. do any of you guys ice fish in the harbour?
Wow, they sure put a lot of time into that to see it in that mess now.
Luckily it happened at 3 in the morning.. and not when 30 men were working inside it earlier in the day on Wednesday. The underground crew thought there was an earthquake !
